Title: Series: Landscapes with biblical subjects and saints
Description: Landscape with St Antony seated in lower right corner, with a pig and tau cross, a castle with a garden at centre, a road with horsemen at right, a small river with swans at left, trees on either side, hills and cities in background; first state before publisher's address; after Lucas Gassel. 1562 Etching and engraving
Producer name: Print made by: Johannes van Doetecum I
Print made by: Lucas van Doetecum
Curator's comments: This is one of a series of five showing landscapes with biblical scenes and saints after Lucas Gassel by Joannes and Lucas Van Doetecum (New Hollstein 291-295), published by Hieronymus Cock in Antwerp in 1652. This series was republished by Nicolaes Lauwers. For another print of this series in BM collection see also 1949,0124.16.
Bibliographic references: New Hollstein (Dutch & Flemish) / The New Hollstein: Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts 1450-1700 (294.I) (The Van Doetecum Family)
Riggs 1977 / Hieronymus Cock, Printmaker and Publisher (103.4)
Associated names: Representation of: St Antony of Egypt
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Capt Edward G Spencer-Churchill
